.TH TETHER 1 "2026-05-24" "0.6.6" "Tether Network Mount Manager"
.SH NAME
tether \- mount and manage network shares from the command line
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tether
.I COMMAND
[OPTIONS]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Tether
is a network mount manager for KDE Plasma on CachyOS and Arch-based
Linux distributions. It provides a guided GUI wizard for connecting to
SMB/CIFS (Windows shares), NFS, and SSHFS network shares, a file
transfer engine built on rsync with progress tracking and resume
support, and a full command-line interface for headless and server use.
.PP
Tether is designed to give Linux newcomers a network file sharing
experience comparable to Windows "Map Network Drive", without requiring
knowledge of mount commands, fstab, or network protocols.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B list
List all configured network mounts and their current connection status.
.TP
.B add
Add and mount a network share interactively. Prompts for protocol,
host, share name, and credentials. Writes an fstab entry so the share
reconnects automatically on login.
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-label \fINAME\fR
Mount label (used as /mnt/NAME). Letters, digits, dash and underscore only.
.TP
.B \-\-protocol \fIPROTO\fR
Protocol: \fBcifs\fR (SMB/Windows), \fBnfs\fR, or \fBsshfs\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-host \fIHOST\fR
Server IP address or hostname.
.TP
.B \-\-path \fISHARE\fR
Share name or export path on the server.
.TP
.B \-\-options \fIOPTS\fR
Extra mount options (e.g. vers=3.0). Optional.
.RE
.TP
.B remove \fILABEL\fR
Unmount a share, remove its fstab entry, and delete its credentials file.
.TP
.B transfer \fISRC\fR \fIDST\fR
Start an rsync file transfer from SRC to DST with progress tracking
and resume support. SRC and DST may be local paths or mounted share
paths (e.g. /mnt/nas/folder).
.TP
.B pause \fIJOB_ID\fR
Pause a running transfer by sending SIGSTOP to the rsync process.
.TP
.B resume \fIJOB_ID\fR
Resume a paused transfer by sending SIGCONT to the rsync process.
.TP
.B cancel \fIJOB_ID\fR
Cancel a transfer. Partial files are kept at the destination (use
\-\-partial to resume later).
.TP
.B watch
Display a live dashboard showing mount status and transfer progress.
Updates every 2 seconds. Press Ctrl+C to exit.
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-interval \fISECS\fR
Update interval in seconds (default: 2).
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/tether/tether.log
Application log file. Contains mount operations, transfer progress,
and diagnostic output.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/tether/mounts.json
Persistent record of configured mounts. Do not edit manually.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/tether/credentials/
Directory for credential files (chmod 700). Used by the file backend
when KWallet is unavailable.
.TP
.I /etc/samba/.tether_LABEL
CIFS credentials file for mount LABEL (root:root, chmod 600).
Written automatically when a CIFS share is added.
.TP
.I /etc/fstab
Tether appends one line per mount, tagged with \fI# tether:LABEL\fR.
These lines are removed automatically when a share is unmounted via
\fBtether remove\fR.
.TP
.I /opt/tether-kde/
Installation directory for all Tether Python source files.
.TP
.I ~/.config/systemd/user/tether-daemon.service
Systemd user service that starts the Tether daemon at login.
.SH DAEMON
Tether runs a persistent background daemon
.RB ( daemon.py )
that registers on the D-Bus session bus as
.IR pro.tether.Daemon .
All GUI and CLI frontends communicate with this daemon rather than
performing privileged operations directly.
.PP
The daemon handles mount/unmount operations, fstab management,
rsync transfer processes, and automatic reconnection of dropped mounts.
Privileged operations (creating mountpoints, writing fstab, mounting)
are performed via
.BR pkexec (1)
helper scripts written to secure temporary files.
.PP
The daemon starts automatically at login via systemd. It can be
managed manually:
.PP
.RS
.nf
systemctl --user start   tether-daemon.service
systemctl --user stop    tether-daemon.service
systemctl --user restart tether-daemon.service
systemctl --user status  tether-daemon.service
.fi
.RE
.SH SECURITY
Tether is designed with security as a primary concern:
.IP \(bu 3
User-supplied strings (host, share name) are validated against a
blocklist of shell metacharacters before use.
.IP \(bu 3
Privileged helper scripts are written to
.BR mkstemp (3)
paths with mode 700 set before content is written, eliminating
race conditions.
.IP \(bu 3
CIFS credentials are stored in
.I /etc/samba/.tether_LABEL
(root:root, chmod 600), not embedded in fstab.
.IP \(bu 3
Credentials are stored in KWallet when available, with a plaintext
chmod 600 file fallback for headless systems.
.IP \(bu 3
All subprocess calls use list arguments — no shell=True, no
command string interpolation.
.SH EXAMPLES
Mount a Windows share interactively:
.PP
.RS
.nf
tether add
.fi
.RE
.PP
Mount a specific share non-interactively:
.PP
.RS
.nf
tether add --label nas --protocol cifs --host 192.168.1.2 --path Media
.fi
.RE
.PP
Check mount status:
.PP
.RS
.nf
tether list
.fi
.RE
.PP
Transfer files from a network share to local storage:
.PP
.RS
.nf
tether transfer /mnt/nas/Photos /home/user/Pictures/Backup
.fi
.RE
.PP
Live dashboard:
.PP
.RS
.nf
tether watch
.fi
.RE
